---
// oxlint-disable-next-line no-unassigned-import
import '../styles/global.css';
import SiteNav from '../components/SiteNav.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <meta name="description" content="Privacy policy for sp00ky." />
    <title>Privacy — sp00ky</title>
  </head>
  <body class="min-h-screen flex flex-col">
    <SiteNav activePath="/privacy" />

    <main class="flex-1">
      <section class="relative pt-24 pb-8 md:pt-32 md:pb-12 overflow-hidden">
        <div
          class="absolute inset-x-0 top-0 h-[420px] pointer-events-none"
          style="background: radial-gradient(60% 50% at 50% 0%, rgba(124,106,239,0.12), transparent 70%);"
        ></div>
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 relative z-10">
          <div class="mb-5">
            <span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 text-[10px] font-medium text-text-muted bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-full uppercase tracking-widest">
              Legal
            </span>
          </div>
          <h1 class="text-section md:text-hero font-semibold text-text-primary mb-4 tracking-tight">
            Privacy Policy
          </h1>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Last updated: April 23, 2026</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="pb-24 md:pb-32">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
          <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-text-tertiary leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and the
              choices you have. It applies to the sp00ky website, documentation, and any managed
              cloud services offered under the sp00ky name (the "Service"). The sp00ky
              open-source library runs on your infrastructure and does not, by itself, send any
              data to us.
            </p>

            <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>We collect a minimal amount of information, in two categories:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>
                <strong>You give us:</strong> account information (such as email address) when
                you sign up for managed services, and any content you choose to submit (for
                example, support messages or feedback).
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Collected automatically:</strong> basic request logs (IP address, user
                agent, referrer, timestamp) and aggregate analytics to measure usage and
                reliability.
              </li>
            </ul>

            <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
            <p>We use information to:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Provide, maintain, and improve the Service.</li>
              <li>Respond to support requests and communicate important updates.</li>
              <li>Detect, prevent, and address abuse, fraud, or security issues.</li>
              <li>Comply with legal obligations.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>3. Sharing</h2>
            <p>
              We do not sell personal information. We share information only with service
              providers that help us operate the Service (such as hosting and analytics
              providers), under appropriate confidentiality and data-protection agreements, or
              when required by law.
            </p>

            <h2>4. Cookies and Similar Technologies</h2>
            <p>
              We use a small number of cookies and similar technologies to keep the Service
              working, remember preferences, and understand aggregate usage. You can control
              cookies in your browser settings.
            </p>

            <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
            <p>
              We keep information only as long as necessary to provide the Service and meet our
              legal obligations. When it is no longer needed, we delete or anonymize it.
            </p>

            <h2>6. Security</h2>
            <p>
              We apply reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect information
              against unauthorized access, loss, or misuse. No system is perfectly secure, and we
              encourage you to use strong credentials and keep your account safe.
            </p>

            <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>
              Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or
              port your personal information, and to object to certain processing. Contact us
              using the details below to exercise these rights.
            </p>

            <h2>8. Children</h2>
            <p>
              The Service is not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect
              personal information from them.
            </p>

            <h2>9. International Transfers</h2>
            <p>
              Your information may be processed in countries other than the one you live in. When
              we transfer data internationally, we apply appropriate safeguards.
            </p>

            <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>
              We may update this policy from time to time. When we do, we will update the "Last
              updated" date above and, for material changes, provide additional notice where
              appropriate.
            </p>

            <h2>11. Contact</h2>
            <p>
              Questions about this policy or our data practices? Open an issue on our
              <a href="https://github.com/mono424/sp00ky" class="text-text-primary underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub repository</a>
              or reach out on
              <a href="https://discord.com/channels/902568124350599239/1454620262526877696" class="text-text-primary underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Discord</a>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <SiteFooter />
  </body>
</html>
